text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia lateriticola is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Pulchellae. It is native to an area in the Peel and South West regions of Western Australia.The ferny-leaved shrub typically grows to a height of 0.4 to 1.5 metres (1 to 5 ft). It blooms from May to October and produces yellow flowers.
